[2026-03-24T20:21:18.476Z] UNKNOWN: {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dy6snuCMx3gaurdBryFGRh","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the project. Let me compile all this information into a clear report:\n\n## Comprehensive Maestro Rust Project Structure Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the maestro project structure. Here's the complete codebase overview for Phase 4 planning:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── main.rs                    # CLI entry point (clap-based)\n├── config.rs                  # maestro.toml parsing\n├── models.rs                  # ModelRouter for label-based model selection\n├── budget.rs                  # BudgetEnforcer for cost limits\n├── prompts.rs                 # PromptBuilder for structured task prompts\n├── util.rs                    # Utility functions\n├── git.rs                     # GitOps trait and CLI implementation\n├── gates/                     # Phase 3 completion gates system\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # CompletionGate enum\n│   └── runner.rs             # GateRunner for executing gates\n├── session/                   # Session management & Claude CLI process control\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # Session, SessionStatus, StreamEvent\n│   ├── manager.rs            # ManagedSession, SessionEvent\n│   ├── pool.rs               # SessionPool with queue/active/finished buckets\n│   ├── parser.rs             # JSON stream parsing from Claude CLI\n│   ├── worktree.rs           # WorktreeManager trait + GitWorktreeManager\n│   ├── health.rs             # HealthMonitor for stall detection\n│   ├── logger.rs             # SessionLogger for transcript logging\n│   ├── cleanup.rs            # CleanupManager for orphaned worktrees\n│   └── retry.rs              # RetryPolicy for session recovery\n├── state/                    # Persistent state management\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # MaestroState (sessions, costs, file claims, issue cache)\n│   ├── store.rs              # StateStore (JSON file persistence)\n│   ├── progress.rs           # ProgressTracker for phase tracking per session\n│   └── file_claims.rs        # FileClaimManager for multi-session file coordination\n├── github/                   # GitHub integration\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # GhIssue, Priority, SessionMode, MaestroLabel\n│   ├── client.rs             # GitHubClient trait + GhCliClient (gh CLI wrapper)\n│   ├── pr.rs                 # PrCreator for PR creation\n│   ├── labels.rs             # LabelManager for maestro:ready/in-progress/done/failed\n│   ├── ci.rs                 # CiChecker for GitHub Actions polling\n│   └── (review, pr, ci modules for Phase 3)\n├── tui/                      # Matrix-style TUI\n│   ├── mod.rs               # Event loop, keyboard handling, TUI::run()\n│   ├── app.rs               # App struct (orchestrates everything)\n│   ├── ui.rs                # draw() function, status bar, activity log\n│   ├── panels.rs            # PanelView for side-by-side session display\n│   ├── detail.rs            # Detail view for single session\n│   ├── activity_log.rs      # ActivityLog widget with scrolling\n│   └── dep_graph.rs         # Dependency graph visualization\n├── work/                    # Work assignment & dependency management\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs             # WorkItem, WorkStatus\n│   ├── assigner.rs          # WorkAssigner with topological sort & priority queue\n│   └── dependencies.rs      # DependencyGraph for cycle detection\n├── notifications/           # Interruption system\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs             # Notification, InterruptLevel\n│   └── dispatcher.rs        # NotificationDispatcher\n└── review/                  # (Phase 3 code review system)\n    ├── mod.rs\n    ├── dispatch.rs\n    └── council.rs\n```\n\n### Cargo.toml Dependencies\n\n**Edition:** 2024 (Rust stable)\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- **clap 4** - CLI argument parsing (derive macros)\n- **ratatui 0.29** - TUI rendering\n- **crossterm 0.28** - Terminal I/O with event-stream\n- **tokio 1** (full features) - Async runtime\n- **serde 1 + serde_json 1** - JSON serialization\n- **toml 0.8** - TOML config parsing\n- **uuid 1** (v4 + serde) - Session IDs\n- **chrono 0.4** - Timestamps\n- **tracing 0.1 + tracing-subscriber 0.3** - Logging to file\n- **anyhow 1** - Error handling\n- **futures 0.3** - Async utilities\n- **tokio-stream 0.1** - Stream utilities\n- **regex 1** - Pattern matching for issue blockers\n- **async-trait 0.1** - Trait method async support\n- **libc 0.2** - Unix signals (SIGSTOP/SIGCONT)\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- **tempfile 3** - Temporary test files\n\n### maestro.toml Configuration Schema\n\n```toml\n[project]\nrepo = \"\"              # Repository path\nbase_branch = \"main\"   # Default branch\n\n[sessions]\nmax_concurrent = 3                          # Session concurrency limit\nstall_timeout_secs = 300                    # Stall detection timeout\ndefault_model = \"opus\"                      # Default LLM model\ndefault_mode = \"orchestrator\"               # Default session mode\npermission_mode = \"bypassPermissions\"       # Claude CLI permission mode\nallowed_tools = []                          # Tool whitelist (empty = all)\nmax_retries = 2                             # Retry attempts for stalled/errored\nretry_cooldown_secs = 60                    # Cooldown between retries\n\n[budget]\nper_session_usd = 5.0                       # Per-session budget\ntotal_usd = 50.0                            # Global budget\nalert_threshold_pct = 80                    # Budget warning threshold\n\n[github]\nissue_filter_labels = [\"maestro:ready\"]     # Labels to fetch issues\nauto_pr = true                              # Create PRs on success\ncache_ttl_secs = 300                        # Issue cache TTL\nauto_merge = false                          # Auto-merge PRs\nmerge_method = \"squash\"                     # merge/squash/rebase\n\n[gates]\nenabled = true                              # Completion gates enabled\ntest_command = \"cargo test\"                 # Default gate command\nci_poll_interval_secs = 30                  # CI status poll interval\nci_max_wait_secs = 1800                     # Max wait for CI\n\n[review]\nenabled = false                             # Review dispatch enabled\ncommand = \"gh pr review ...\"                # Review command template\nauto_approve = false                        # Auto-approve after review\n\n[notifications]\ndesktop = true                              # Desktop notifications\nslack = false                               # Slack notifications\n\n[models]\n# routing = { \"priority:P0\" = \"opus\", \"type:docs\" = \"haiku\" }\n\n[concurrency]\nheavy_task_labels = []                      # Heavy task marker labels\nheavy_task_limit = 2                        # Max concurrent heavy tasks\n\n[monitoring]\nwork_tick_interval_secs = 10                # Work assigner update interval\n```\n\n### Core Data Types & Structures\n\n**Session State Machine:**\n```rust\npub enum SessionStatus {\n    Queued,     // Waiting for slot\n    Spawning,   // Starting Claude CLI process\n    Running,    // Active and producing output\n    Completed,  // Success\n    Errored,    // Failed\n    Paused,     // Paused (SIGSTOP)\n    Killed,     // Manually killed\n    Stalled,    // No activity timeout\n    Retrying,   // Attempting retry\n}\n```\n\n**Session Stream Events:**\n```rust\npub enum StreamEvent {\n    AssistantMessage { text: String },\n    ToolUse { tool: String, file_path: Option<String>, args_preview: String },\n    ToolResult { tool: String, is_error: bool },\n    CostUpdate { cost_usd: f64 },\n    Completed { cost_usd: f64 },\n    Error { message: String },\n    Unknown { raw: String },\n}\n```\n\n**Work Item & Status:**\n```rust\npub enum WorkStatus { Pending, Blocked, InProgress, Done, Failed }\npub struct WorkItem {\n    pub priority: Priority,                 // P0, P1, P2\n    pub mode: Option<SessionMode>,          // Orchestrator, Vibe\n    pub status: WorkStatus,\n    pub blocked_by: Vec<u64>,              // Dependency issue numbers\n    pub issue: GhIssue,\n}\n```\n\n**GitHub Issue Metadata:**\n```rust\npub struct GhIssue {\n    pub number: u64,\n    pub title: String,\n    pub body: String,\n    pub labels: Vec<String>,\n    pub state: String,\n    pub html_url: String,\n}\n\npub enum Priority { P0 = 0, P1 = 1, P2 = 2 }\npub enum SessionMode { Orchestrator, Vibe }\npub enum MaestroLabel { Ready, InProgress, Done, Failed }\n```\n\n**MaestroState (Persistent):**\n```rust\npub struct MaestroState {\n    pub sessions: Vec<Session>,              // All sessions (active + finished + queued)\n    pub total_cost_usd: f64,                // Aggregate cost\n    pub file_claims: HashMap<String, Uuid>,  // File → owning session\n    pub last_updated: Option<DateTime<Utc>>,\n    pub issue_cache: HashMap<u64, GhIssue>,  // Cached GitHub data\n}\n```\n\n### Key Struct Relationships\n\n**App Struct** (orchestration hub in src/tui/app.rs):\n- `pool: SessionPool` - Session lifecycle management\n- `work_assigner: Option<WorkAssigner>` - GitHub issue queue\n- `github_client: Option<Box<dyn GitHubClient>>` - API calls\n- `config: Option<Config>` - Runtime configuration\n- `budget_enforcer: Option<BudgetEnforcer>` - Cost limits\n- `model_router: Option<ModelRouter>` - Label → model mapping\n- `health_monitor: Box<dyn HealthCheck>` - Stall detection\n- `progress_tracker: ProgressTracker` - Phase tracking per session\n- `notifications: NotificationDispatcher` - Interruptions\n- `activity_log: ActivityLog` - UI log widget\n- `panel_view: PanelView` - Side-by-side panels\n- `state: MaestroState` - Persistent state\n- `store: StateStore` - JSON persistence\n\n**SessionPool** (src/session/pool.rs):\n- `queue: VecDeque<Session>` - Queued sessions\n- `active: Vec<ManagedSession>` - Running sessions\n- `finished: Vec<ManagedSession>` - Completed sessions\n- `worktree_mgr: Box<dyn WorktreeManager>` - Git worktree creation\n- `file_claims: FileClaimManager` - Multi-session file coordination\n- `event_tx: mpsc::UnboundedSender<SessionEvent>` - Event channel\n\n**ManagedSession** (src/session/manager.rs):\n- `session: Session` - Core session data\n- `child: Option<Child>` - Claude CLI subprocess\n- `worktree_path: Option<PathBuf>` - Git worktree directory\n- `branch_name: Option<String>` - maestro/issue-N branch\n- `system_prompt_appendix: Option<String>` - File claims injection\n- `permission_mode: Option<String>` - Claude CLI permission mode\n- `allowed_tools: Vec<String>` - Tool whitelist\n\n### TUI Architecture\n\n**Event Loop** (src/tui/mod.rs):\n1. Draw current state with ratatui\n2. Non-blocking drain of `event_rx` channel (SessionEvent messages)\n3. Process session events (cost, tool use, completion)\n4. Check completions & promote queued sessions\n5. Poll keyboard input with 50ms timeout\n6. Route keyboard to App state mutations\n7. Auto-exit when all sessions terminal + 30s timeout\n\n**Display Modes** (TuiMode enum):\n- `Overview` - Side-by-side panels of active/finished sessions\n- `Detail(usize)` - Full detail view for session[idx] with progress phases\n- `DependencyGraph` - Issue dependency visualization\n\n**Rendering** (src/tui/ui.rs):\n- 3-row layout: status bar (elapsed, active count, budget) + content + activity log\n- Status bar: MAESTRO v0.1.0 | 3 agents (2 active) | $10.50/$50.00 | 00:15:30\n- Activity log: scrollable history of all session events\n- Notification banner overlay for critical/blocker interrupts\n\n### Key Algorithms\n\n**WorkAssigner** (src/work/assigner.rs):\n- Topological sort of issues by dependencies (detects cycles)\n- Priority queue: P0 > P1 > P2, then topo order, then issue number\n- `next_ready()` returns next N issues (respects heavy task limits)\n- `mark_failed_cascade()` propagates failure to dependents via BFS\n- `mark_done()` unblocks transitive dependents\n\n**BudgetEnforcer** (src/budget.rs):\n- Per-session limit: kill if session_cost >= per_session_usd\n- Global limit: kill if total_cost >= total_usd\n- Alert threshold: emit warning at alert_threshold_pct\n- Deduplication: `record_alert()` prevents duplicate warnings\n\n**HealthMonitor** (src/session/health.rs):\n- Records timestamp of last activity per session_id\n- `check_stalls()` identifies sessions inactive > stall_timeout_secs\n- Moves stalled sessions to retry queue\n\n### Claude CLI Integration\n\n**Process Invocation** (src/session/manager.rs:spawn):\n```rust\nclaude --print --verbose --output-format stream-json \\\n    --model {model} \\\n    --permission-mode {mode} \\\n    --allowedTools {tools} \\\n    --append-system-prompt \"{file_claims}\" \\\n    \"{prompt}\"\n```\n\n**Streaming Output:**\n- Lines are parsed by `parse_stream_line()` (src/session/parser.rs)\n- Events sent via mpsc channel to TUI\n- Transcript logged per session for debugging\n\n**File Claims Injection:**\n- `FileClaimManager` builds system prompt appendix\n- Lists all files claimed by other active sessions\n- Claude prompted to avoid conflicts\n\n### Build & Test Commands\n\n```bash\ncargo build                 # Debug build\ncargo build --release       # Release build\ncargo test                  # Run all tests\ncargo clippy               # Lint checks\ncargo fmt                  # Format code\n```\n\n### Critical File Paths for Phase 4\n\n**State Persistence:**\n- `/maestro-state.json` - Runtime state (sessions, costs, claims, cache)\n- `~/.maestro/logs/` - Session transcripts by session_id\n\n**Git Integration:**\n- `./.maestro/worktrees/` - Session-specific git worktrees\n- Branches: `maestro/issue-{N}` or `maestro/session-{8-char-uuid}`\n\n**Logging:**\n- `./maestro.log` - Debug logs from tracing subscriber\n\nAll the above files are ready for Phase 4 implementation. The architecture is modular with clear separation of concerns: session management, TUI rendering, GitHub integration, work assignment, and budget enforcement."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a88a7ef9141aebacc (use SendMessage with to: 'a88a7ef9141aebacc' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 94749\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 59875</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aee246ba-d48a-45db-9f9e-2baf98ff22c0","uuid":"ae8f44e2-ae66-40e9-85e5-7793d4705ff6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:21:18.461Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the maestro Rust project structure. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory tree - all src/ files and their modules\n2. The current Cargo.toml dependencies\n3. The config.rs file (how maestro.toml is parsed)\n4. The main.rs file (CLI entry point, clap commands)\n5. The tui/app.rs file (app state, event handling)\n6. The tui/ui.rs file (rendering)\n7. Any existing module declarations (mod.rs files)\n8. The session types and manager\n\nRead ALL of these files completely and provide their full contents. This is critical for planning Phase 4 implementation.","agentId":"a88a7ef9141aebacc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive view of the project. Let me compile all this information into a clear report:\n\n## Comprehensive Maestro Rust Project Structure Analysis\n\nI've thoroughly explored the maestro project structure. Here's the complete codebase overview for Phase 4 planning:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── main.rs                    # CLI entry point (clap-based)\n├── config.rs                  # maestro.toml parsing\n├── models.rs                  # ModelRouter for label-based model selection\n├── budget.rs                  # BudgetEnforcer for cost limits\n├── prompts.rs                 # PromptBuilder for structured task prompts\n├── util.rs                    # Utility functions\n├── git.rs                     # GitOps trait and CLI implementation\n├── gates/                     # Phase 3 completion gates system\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # CompletionGate enum\n│   └── runner.rs             # GateRunner for executing gates\n├── session/                   # Session management & Claude CLI process control\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # Session, SessionStatus, StreamEvent\n│   ├── manager.rs            # ManagedSession, SessionEvent\n│   ├── pool.rs               # SessionPool with queue/active/finished buckets\n│   ├── parser.rs             # JSON stream parsing from Claude CLI\n│   ├── worktree.rs           # WorktreeManager trait + GitWorktreeManager\n│   ├── health.rs             # HealthMonitor for stall detection\n│   ├── logger.rs             # SessionLogger for transcript logging\n│   ├── cleanup.rs            # CleanupManager for orphaned worktrees\n│   └── retry.rs              # RetryPolicy for session recovery\n├── state/                    # Persistent state management\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # MaestroState (sessions, costs, file claims, issue cache)\n│   ├── store.rs              # StateStore (JSON file persistence)\n│   ├── progress.rs           # ProgressTracker for phase tracking per session\n│   └── file_claims.rs        # FileClaimManager for multi-session file coordination\n├── github/                   # GitHub integration\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs              # GhIssue, Priority, SessionMode, MaestroLabel\n│   ├── client.rs             # GitHubClient trait + GhCliClient (gh CLI wrapper)\n│   ├── pr.rs                 # PrCreator for PR creation\n│   ├── labels.rs             # LabelManager for maestro:ready/in-progress/done/failed\n│   ├── ci.rs                 # CiChecker for GitHub Actions polling\n│   └── (review, pr, ci modules for Phase 3)\n├── tui/                      # Matrix-style TUI\n│   ├── mod.rs               # Event loop, keyboard handling, TUI::run()\n│   ├── app.rs               # App struct (orchestrates everything)\n│   ├── ui.rs                # draw() function, status bar, activity log\n│   ├── panels.rs            # PanelView for side-by-side session display\n│   ├── detail.rs            # Detail view for single session\n│   ├── activity_log.rs      # ActivityLog widget with scrolling\n│   └── dep_graph.rs         # Dependency graph visualization\n├── work/                    # Work assignment & dependency management\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs             # WorkItem, WorkStatus\n│   ├── assigner.rs          # WorkAssigner with topological sort & priority queue\n│   └── dependencies.rs      # DependencyGraph for cycle detection\n├── notifications/           # Interruption system\n│   ├── mod.rs\n│   ├── types.rs             # Notification, InterruptLevel\n│   └── dispatcher.rs        # NotificationDispatcher\n└── review/                  # (Phase 3 code review system)\n    ├── mod.rs\n    ├── dispatch.rs\n    └── council.rs\n```\n\n### Cargo.toml Dependencies\n\n**Edition:** 2024 (Rust stable)\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- **clap 4** - CLI argument parsing (derive macros)\n- **ratatui 0.29** - TUI rendering\n- **crossterm 0.28** - Terminal I/O with event-stream\n- **tokio 1** (full features) - Async runtime\n- **serde 1 + serde_json 1** - JSON serialization\n- **toml 0.8** - TOML config parsing\n- **uuid 1** (v4 + serde) - Session IDs\n- **chrono 0.4** - Timestamps\n- **tracing 0.1 + tracing-subscriber 0.3** - Logging to file\n- **anyhow 1** - Error handling\n- **futures 0.3** - Async utilities\n- **tokio-stream 0.1** - Stream utilities\n- **regex 1** - Pattern matching for issue blockers\n- **async-trait 0.1** - Trait method async support\n- **libc 0.2** - Unix signals (SIGSTOP/SIGCONT)\n\n**Dev Dependencies:**\n- **tempfile 3** - Temporary test files\n\n### maestro.toml Configuration Schema\n\n```toml\n[project]\nrepo = \"\"              # Repository path\nbase_branch = \"main\"   # Default branch\n\n[sessions]\nmax_concurrent = 3                          # Session concurrency limit\nstall_timeout_secs = 300                    # Stall detection timeout\ndefault_model = \"opus\"                      # Default LLM model\ndefault_mode = \"orchestrator\"               # Default session mode\npermission_mode = \"bypassPermissions\"       # Claude CLI permission mode\nallowed_tools = []                          # Tool whitelist (empty = all)\nmax_retries = 2                             # Retry attempts for stalled/errored\nretry_cooldown_secs = 60                    # Cooldown between retries\n\n[budget]\nper_session_usd = 5.0                       # Per-session budget\ntotal_usd = 50.0                            # Global budget\nalert_threshold_pct = 80                    # Budget warning threshold\n\n[github]\nissue_filter_labels = [\"maestro:ready\"]     # Labels to fetch issues\nauto_pr = true                              # Create PRs on success\ncache_ttl_secs = 300                        # Issue cache TTL\nauto_merge = false                          # Auto-merge PRs\nmerge_method = \"squash\"                     # merge/squash/rebase\n\n[gates]\nenabled = true                              # Completion gates enabled\ntest_command = \"cargo test\"                 # Default gate command\nci_poll_interval_secs = 30                  # CI status poll interval\nci_max_wait_secs = 1800                     # Max wait for CI\n\n[review]\nenabled = false                             # Review dispatch enabled\ncommand = \"gh pr review ...\"                # Review command template\nauto_approve = false                        # Auto-approve after review\n\n[notifications]\ndesktop = true                              # Desktop notifications\nslack = false                               # Slack notifications\n\n[models]\n# routing = { \"priority:P0\" = \"opus\", \"type:docs\" = \"haiku\" }\n\n[concurrency]\nheavy_task_labels = []                      # Heavy task marker labels\nheavy_task_limit = 2                        # Max concurrent heavy tasks\n\n[monitoring]\nwork_tick_interval_secs = 10                # Work assigner update interval\n```\n\n### Core Data Types & Structures\n\n**Session State Machine:**\n```rust\npub enum SessionStatus {\n    Queued,     // Waiting for slot\n    Spawning,   // Starting Claude CLI process\n    Running,    // Active and producing output\n    Completed,  // Success\n    Errored,    // Failed\n    Paused,     // Paused (SIGSTOP)\n    Killed,     // Manually killed\n    Stalled,    // No activity timeout\n    Retrying,   // Attempting retry\n}\n```\n\n**Session Stream Events:**\n```rust\npub enum StreamEvent {\n    AssistantMessage { text: String },\n    ToolUse { tool: String, file_path: Option<String>, args_preview: String },\n    ToolResult { tool: String, is_error: bool },\n    CostUpdate { cost_usd: f64 },\n    Completed { cost_usd: f64 },\n    Error { message: String },\n    Unknown { raw: String },\n}\n```\n\n**Work Item & Status:**\n```rust\npub enum WorkStatus { Pending, Blocked, InProgress, Done, Failed }\npub struct WorkItem {\n    pub priority: Priority,                 // P0, P1, P2\n    pub mode: Option<SessionMode>,          // Orchestrator, Vibe\n    pub status: WorkStatus,\n    pub blocked_by: Vec<u64>,              // Dependency issue numbers\n    pub issue: GhIssue,\n}\n```\n\n**GitHub Issue Metadata:**\n```rust\npub struct GhIssue {\n    pub number: u64,\n    pub title: String,\n    pub body: String,\n    pub labels: Vec<String>,\n    pub state: String,\n    pub html_url: String,\n}\n\npub enum Priority { P0 = 0, P1 = 1, P2 = 2 }\npub enum SessionMode { Orchestrator, Vibe }\npub enum MaestroLabel { Ready, InProgress, Done, Failed }\n```\n\n**MaestroState (Persistent):**\n```rust\npub struct MaestroState {\n    pub sessions: Vec<Session>,              // All sessions (active + finished + queued)\n    pub total_cost_usd: f64,                // Aggregate cost\n    pub file_claims: HashMap<String, Uuid>,  // File → owning session\n    pub last_updated: Option<DateTime<Utc>>,\n    pub issue_cache: HashMap<u64, GhIssue>,  // Cached GitHub data\n}\n```\n\n### Key Struct Relationships\n\n**App Struct** (orchestration hub in src/tui/app.rs):\n- `pool: SessionPool` - Session lifecycle management\n- `work_assigner: Option<WorkAssigner>` - GitHub issue queue\n- `github_client: Option<Box<dyn GitHubClient>>` - API calls\n- `config: Option<Config>` - Runtime configuration\n- `budget_enforcer: Option<BudgetEnforcer>` - Cost limits\n- `model_router: Option<ModelRouter>` - Label → model mapping\n- `health_monitor: Box<dyn HealthCheck>` - Stall detection\n- `progress_tracker: ProgressTracker` - Phase tracking per session\n- `notifications: NotificationDispatcher` - Interruptions\n- `activity_log: ActivityLog` - UI log widget\n- `panel_view: PanelView` - Side-by-side panels\n- `state: MaestroState` - Persistent state\n- `store: StateStore` - JSON persistence\n\n**SessionPool** (src/session/pool.rs):\n- `queue: VecDeque<Session>` - Queued sessions\n- `active: Vec<ManagedSession>` - Running sessions\n- `finished: Vec<ManagedSession>` - Completed sessions\n- `worktree_mgr: Box<dyn WorktreeManager>` - Git worktree creation\n- `file_claims: FileClaimManager` - Multi-session file coordination\n- `event_tx: mpsc::UnboundedSender<SessionEvent>` - Event channel\n\n**ManagedSession** (src/session/manager.rs):\n- `session: Session` - Core session data\n- `child: Option<Child>` - Claude CLI subprocess\n- `worktree_path: Option<PathBuf>` - Git worktree directory\n- `branch_name: Option<String>` - maestro/issue-N branch\n- `system_prompt_appendix: Option<String>` - File claims injection\n- `permission_mode: Option<String>` - Claude CLI permission mode\n- `allowed_tools: Vec<String>` - Tool whitelist\n\n### TUI Architecture\n\n**Event Loop** (src/tui/mod.rs):\n1. Draw current state with ratatui\n2. Non-blocking drain of `event_rx` channel (SessionEvent messages)\n3. Process session events (cost, tool use, completion)\n4. Check completions & promote queued sessions\n5. Poll keyboard input with 50ms timeout\n6. Route keyboard to App state mutations\n7. Auto-exit when all sessions terminal + 30s timeout\n\n**Display Modes** (TuiMode enum):\n- `Overview` - Side-by-side panels of active/finished sessions\n- `Detail(usize)` - Full detail view for session[idx] with progress phases\n- `DependencyGraph` - Issue dependency visualization\n\n**Rendering** (src/tui/ui.rs):\n- 3-row layout: status bar (elapsed, active count, budget) + content + activity log\n- Status bar: MAESTRO v0.1.0 | 3 agents (2 active) | $10.50/$50.00 | 00:15:30\n- Activity log: scrollable history of all session events\n- Notification banner overlay for critical/blocker interrupts\n\n### Key Algorithms\n\n**WorkAssigner** (src/work/assigner.rs):\n- Topological sort of issues by dependencies (detects cycles)\n- Priority queue: P0 > P1 > P2, then topo order, then issue number\n- `next_ready()` returns next N issues (respects heavy task limits)\n- `mark_failed_cascade()` propagates failure to dependents via BFS\n- `mark_done()` unblocks transitive dependents\n\n**BudgetEnforcer** (src/budget.rs):\n- Per-session limit: kill if session_cost >= per_session_usd\n- Global limit: kill if total_cost >= total_usd\n- Alert threshold: emit warning at alert_threshold_pct\n- Deduplication: `record_alert()` prevents duplicate warnings\n\n**HealthMonitor** (src/session/health.rs):\n- Records timestamp of last activity per session_id\n- `check_stalls()` identifies sessions inactive > stall_timeout_secs\n- Moves stalled sessions to retry queue\n\n### Claude CLI Integration\n\n**Process Invocation** (src/session/manager.rs:spawn):\n```rust\nclaude --print --verbose --output-format stream-json \\\n    --model {model} \\\n    --permission-mode {mode} \\\n    --allowedTools {tools} \\\n    --append-system-prompt \"{file_claims}\" \\\n    \"{prompt}\"\n```\n\n**Streaming Output:**\n- Lines are parsed by `parse_stream_line()` (src/session/parser.rs)\n- Events sent via mpsc channel to TUI\n- Transcript logged per session for debugging\n\n**File Claims Injection:**\n- `FileClaimManager` builds system prompt appendix\n- Lists all files claimed by other active sessions\n- Claude prompted to avoid conflicts\n\n### Build & Test Commands\n\n```bash\ncargo build                 # Debug build\ncargo build --release       # Release build\ncargo test                  # Run all tests\ncargo clippy               # Lint checks\ncargo fmt                  # Format code\n```\n\n### Critical File Paths for Phase 4\n\n**State Persistence:**\n- `/maestro-state.json` - Runtime state (sessions, costs, claims, cache)\n- `~/.maestro/logs/` - Session transcripts by session_id\n\n**Git Integration:**\n- `./.maestro/worktrees/` - Session-specific git worktrees\n- Branches: `maestro/issue-{N}` or `maestro/session-{8-char-uuid}`\n\n**Logging:**\n- `./maestro.log` - Debug logs from tracing subscriber\n\nAll the above files are ready for Phase 4 implementation. The architecture is modular with clear separation of concerns: session management, TUI rendering, GitHub integration, work assignment, and budget enforcement."}],"totalDurationMs":59875,"totalTokens":94749,"totalToolUseCount":22,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1157,"cache_read_input_tokens":89668,"output_tokens":3918,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1157},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
